<TITLE> ACC official allegedly burns wife </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 20 (bdnews24.com)--An official of the Anticorruption Commission allegedly doused his wife with kerosene and burned her in the capital's Motijheel on Sunday. Khandaker Mesbah Uddin, an assistant director with the ACC, poured paraffin on 30-year old Salma Akhter, a mother of two, her elder sister Bilkis Hossain told bdnews24.com. He had been torturing her since their wedding, she further alleged. Salma was admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital's burns unit and her condition is stated to be critical. The whole body is burnt, said Limon Kumar Dhar, the emergency medical officer at the burns unit. bdnews2
